<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="43" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/1019: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi></persName>)<note n="70" xml:id="d43fn70">Similar
                                telegrams were sent to the American missions in Ecuador, Nicaragua,
                                and Honduras.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-05T17:00:00-05:00">March 5, 1934—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>16. Your telegram No. 20, March 2, 4 p.m.<note n="71" xml:id="d43fn71">Not printed.</note> You may inform the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            orally that the Department has received a similar telegram, that the
                            American Government’s policy of nonrecognition of Manchukuo remains
                            unchanged and that all messages received here from that source are filed
                            without acknowledgment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>